TYPHOID FEVER UPDATE 2007 (11)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
In this update:
[1] India (Andhra Pradesh)
[2] Philippines (Mindanao)
******
[1] India (Andhra Pradesh)
Date: Mon 16 Jul 2007
Source: The Siasat Daily [edited]
<http://www.siasat.com/english/index.php?option=content&task=view&id=194335&Itemid=79&cattitle=Hyderabad>

Typhoid is threatening to run amuck in parts of the old city of
Hyderabad, while the urban health centers of the district health
department have been acting as a mute witness to the spurt in
infirmities. Neither the health centers nor the health camps are able
to effectively extend medical facilities to the needy.
On the contrary, the private clinics are coming to the rescue by
keeping their doors open even up to 11 pm. for patients. Typhoid and
other fevers have gripped the Teegalakunta, Nawab Saab Kunta, Ansari
Road, Kaalapathar, Bilalnagar, and Ramnaspura areas of the old city.
On Sun 15 Jul 2007, alone, about 6 typhoid patients were admitted to
private clinics of Bilalnagar, Ramnaspura, and Kaalapathar.
"The civic situation is appalling here. Drinking water supply gets
mixed up with sewage leading to such outbreaks," says Dr. Khateeja
Begum of Makkah Health Center, Kaalapathar.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Hyderabad is the capital city of the Indian province of Andhra
